\label{conj:caterpillar}
Let  $T$ be a fully leafed Penrose subtree. 
\begin{enumerate}[(i)]
\item If $T$ is saturated then $T $ is a caterpillar.
\item If $T$ is non saturated, then there exists a saturated caterpillar $T_1$ and an appendix $T_2$ such that $T=T_{1}\diamond T_{2}$.
\end{enumerate}

